| style="text-align:left;" colspan="5"|Also noteworthy, Harper et al in the conclusion of their paper make the following remark: ''"In a sense, the derived distance of 200 pc is a balance between the 131 pc（425 ly）Hipparcos distance and the radio which tends towards 250 [[parsec|pc]]（815 [[Light_year|ly]]）"''—hence establishing ± 815 [[Light_year|ly]] as the outside distance for the star.
